{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638678","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638678"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:57:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:57:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17728"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17728","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17728"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.9,0,0.03,0.03,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10442"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76189"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10442","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10442"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17728"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61693"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"44"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"417"},{"type":"tags","id":"4631"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4978"},{"type":"tags","id":"5230"},{"type":"tags","id":"5800"},{"type":"tags","id":"10331"},{"type":"tags","id":"11207"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24384"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24388"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76189","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76189"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EYou are giving a presentation to the Anaesthetics department on the multi-modal approach to pain management.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the role of cannabinoids in pain management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adjunctive therapy for chronic pain when conventional treatments fail","First-line treatment for neuropathic pain, both acute and chronic","Adjunctive treatment for acute pain if there is a neuropathic element","Recommended for use in all patients with chronic pain due to minimal side effects","Mildly effective for all types of pain, both acute and chronic"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdjunctive therapy for chronic pain when conventional treatments fail\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes the current role that cannabinoids may take in pain management. While cannabinoids may be considered as part of a multimodal approach to chronic pain management, further evidence is needed to establish which patient populations will benefit and by how much. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFirst-line treatment for neuropathic pain, both acute and chronic\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. For neuropathic pain, first-line treatments typically include anticonvulsants (like gabapentin or pregabalin) or antidepressants. Cannabinoids, if used, would be considered further down the line of therapeutic options. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdjunctive treatment for acute pain if there is a neuropathic element\u003C/strong\u003E is not appropriate. Cannabinoids are not recommended for acute pain management, regardless of whether there is a neuropathic component. Acute pain is typically managed with other medications such as non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs or short-term opioids if necessary.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecommended for use in all patients with chronic pain due to minimal side effects\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Cannabinoids can have significant side effects including sedation, dizziness, cognitive impairment, and potential for dependence. They are not suitable for all patients and should be prescribed selectively.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMildly effective for all types of pain, both acute and chronic\u003C/strong\u003E is not accurate. The evidence for cannabinoid efficacy varies significantly depending on the type of pain. Some patients may experience significant benefit while others may have little to no response. The evidence is strongest for specific types of chronic pain, particularly neuropathic pain. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe use of cannabinoids in pain management requires careful patient selection, monitoring, and should be part of a comprehensive pain management strategy that includes non-pharmacological approaches. Regular review of efficacy and side effects is essential.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cannabinoids may be considered for chronic pain management when conventional therapies are inadequate.","Evidence for the efficacy of cannabinoids in pain management varies by pain type.","Cannabinoids do not have a role in acute pain management"],"references":["Romero-Sandoval EA, Kolano AL, Alvarado-V\u00e1zquez PA. Cannabis and Cannabinoids for Chronic Pain. Curr Rheumatol Rep. 2017 Oct 5;19(11):67. doi: 10.1007/s11926-017-0693-1. PMID: 28983880.","Longo R, Oudshoorn A, Befus D. Cannabis for Chronic Pain: A Rapid Systematic Review of Randomized Control Trials. Pain Manag Nurs. 2021 Apr;22(2):141-149. doi: 10.1016/j.pmn.2020.11.006. Epub 2021 Jan 19. PMID: 33353819.","Hameed M, Prasad S, Jain E, Dogrul BN, Al-Oleimat A, Pokhrel B, Chowdhury S, Co EL, Mitra S, Quinonez J, Ruxmohan S, Stein J. Medical Cannabis for Chronic Nonmalignant Pain Management. Curr Pain Headache Rep. 2023 Apr;27(4):57-63. doi: 10.1007/s11916-023-01101-w. Epub 2023 Mar 10. PMID: 36897501; PMCID: PMC9999073."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61693"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17728"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61693"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-02T11:25:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-02T11:26:23+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10442"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76189"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"44","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/44"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude79","name":"Pain Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.eme